I think we can check the component using the JIRA public API ( for example https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/ARROW-13674 ) where
{code}
"components":[
    {"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/component/12333244","id":"12333244","name":"Continuous Integration"}, 
    {"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/component/12334506","id":"12334506","name":"Developer Tools"}
]
{code}

What should we do if the component is missing? I think the simplest thing would be to leave a comment on the GitHub PR as writing comments or touching the jira issue would probably require API write privileges which seems would make the thing much more complex (private tokens etc) for a minor difference.
